            <span class="section-title__tagline editable">Motion Design</span>
            <h2 class="section-title__title editable">Animations & Interactions</h2>
            <p class="editable" style="max-width: 700px; margin: 20px auto;">
                Subtle animations enhance the user experience and draw attention to interactive elements.
            </p>
        </div>

        <div class="row" style="margin-bottom: 40px;">
            <div class="col-lg-4">
                <div style="background: white; padding: 30px; border-radius: 12px; margin-bottom: 30px; box-shadow: 0 4px 15px rgba(0,0,0,0.08);">
                    <h5 style="color: #005282; margin-bottom: 15px; font-weight: 700;">Slide-In Animations</h5>
                    <p style="font-size: 14px;">Buttons and CTAs slide in from the right on scroll to draw attention.</p>
                    <pre style="background: #f8f9fa; padding: 15px; border-radius: 8px; font-size: 11px; overflow-x: auto; margin-top: 15px;"><code>@keyframes slideInFromRight {
  0% {
    opacity: 0;
    transform: translateX(50px);
  }
  100% {
    opacity: 1;
    transform: translateX(0);
  }
}</code></pre>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="col-lg-4">
                <div style="background: white; padding: 30px; border-radius: 12px; margin-bottom: 30px; box-shadow: 0 4px 15px rgba(0,0,0,0.08);">
                    <h5 style="color: #005282; margin-bottom: 15px; font-weight: 700;">Number Scramble</h5>
                    <p style="font-size: 14px;">Stats animate with counting effect using Intersection Observer for scroll triggers.</p>
                    <pre style="background: #f8f9fa; padding: 15px; border-radius: 8px; font-size: 11px; overflow-x: auto; margin-top: 15px;"><code>/* Stable number widths */
.stat-number {
  font-variant-numeric:
    tabular-nums;
  text-align: center;
  width: 100%;
}</code></pre>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="col-lg-4">
                <div style="background: white; padding: 30px; border-radius: 12px; margin-bottom: 30px; box-shadow: 0 4px 15px rgba(0,0,0,0.08);">
                    <h5 style="color: #005282; margin-bottom: 15px; font-weight: 700;">Hover Effects</h5>
                    <p style="font-size: 14px;">Cards and buttons lift on hover with subtle shadow changes.</p>
                    <pre style="background: #f8f9fa; padding: 15px; border-radius: 8px; font-size: 11px; overflow-x: auto; margin-top: 15px;"><code>.card:hover {
  transform:
    translateY(-5px);
  box-shadow:
    0 8px 25px
    rgba(0,0,0,0.15);
}</code></pre>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="row">
            <div class="col-lg-6">
